comments.message:
Created https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/50887 to address the dbus property for NTP servers

@Asmitha - as per https://github.com/systemd/systemd/issues/22384 ; the listed NTP servers at timesyncd need not be written to the interface specific network config file. This is a system level configuration and can be copied to /etc/systemd/timesyncd.conf

Similar to NameServers, we need DMTF redfish schema changes to list the NTP servers as well. I will create an issue for redfish as well.

@asmitha and @sunitha: Can we take a look at https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/master/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Network/EthernetInterface.interface.yaml and introduce one more property Static NTP servers same as DNS.

StaticNTPServers: shows the NTP server details from the network configuration file.
ntpServers: shows the ntp server details from the timesyncd.
